{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852794496,"sessionID":"ses_286ed4f0bffefmfnGF4OM7xCV9","part":{"id":"prt_d7913325d001idzM4v342rrhK2","messageID":"msg_d791327c0001ippA85ivfqHqne","sessionID":"ses_286ed4f0bffefmfnGF4OM7xCV9","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-ace984b17fda4d038360418d068884b0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-store/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-store/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Store Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Store interface contract\n9: The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n12: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n13: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n14: - **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Not found semantics\n17: The system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Get missing session\n20: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n21: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs\n22: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Session key naming\n25: The system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Key construction\n28: - **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n29: - **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n30: - **THEN** the string key is `session:abc`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Expiry index\n33: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL add the member with the sandbox expiry score. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL remove the member.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n36: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n37: - **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n38: - **THEN** it selects members with scores from negative infinity through `before.Unix()`, limited to `limit` entries\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Last-activity index\n41: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD with score `time.Now().Unix()` on initial store. `UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD with the provided timestamp (or now if zero). `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM the member.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n44: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n45: - **WHEN** executed\n46: - **THEN** members with last-activity score Ōēż `before.Unix()` are returned up to `limit`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: StoreSandbox atomicity and validation\n49: The system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch errors.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n52: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n53: - **WHEN** called\n54: - **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: UpdateSandbox semantics\n57: The system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries in this operation.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Missing key on update\n60: - **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n61: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs\n62: - **THEN** Redis: SETXX returns false ŌåÆ error `key not exists`; Valkey: response not OK ŌåÆ same error class\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID cleanup\n65: The system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Full removal\n68: - **GIVEN** an existing session\n69: - **WHEN** delete succeeds\n70: - **THEN** GET session key returns not found and ZSETs no longer contain the member\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: List loaders tolerate missing keys\n73: When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing (Redis pipeline GET nil, Valkey MGET empty string) without failing the whole batch.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member\n76: - **GIVEN** a session id in ZSET without a hash/string value\n77: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\n78: - **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity preconditions\n81: The system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n84: - **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key\n85: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n86: - **THEN** return `ErrNotFound`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\n89: The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Default redis\n92: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n93: - **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n94: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Redis environment and password policy\n97: The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n100: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set and `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n101: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n102: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Valkey environment and options\n105: The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses split for `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Optional client flags\n108: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n109: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n110: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is true on `ClientOption`\n111: \n112: ### Requirement: Singleton access\n113: The system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Single initialization\n116: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()`\n117: - **WHEN** they run concurrently\n118: - **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n\n(End of file - total 118 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Store Specification\n\n## Purpose\nPersist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Store interface contract\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n\n### Requirement: Not found semantics\nThe system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n\n#### Scenario: Get missing session\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-store/spec.md","time":{"start":1775852794488,"end":1775852794494}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852794507,"sessionID":"ses_286ed4f0bffefmfnGF4OM7xCV9","part":{"id":"prt_d79132ffd001x8W5TNTwiDLL62","messageID":"msg_d791327c0001ippA85ivfqHqne","sessionID":"ses_286ed4f0bffefmfnGF4OM7xCV9","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9b9736de0a0d47f69998314d3c837366","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-store/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-store/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Store ŌĆö Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` ŌĆö versions in sandbox-orchestration `design.md`.\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n8: \n9: ### Store interface (exact signatures)\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: package store\n13: \n14: import (\n15:     \"context\"\n16:     \"time\"\n17: \n18:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n19: )\n20: \n21: type Store interface {\n22:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n23:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n24:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n25:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n26:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n27:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n28:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n29:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n30:     Close() error\n31: }\n32: ```\n33: \n34: ### Errors\n35: \n36: ```go\n37: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n38: ```\n39: \n40: ### Provider type constants (`singleton.go`)\n41: \n42: ```go\n43: const (\n44:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n45:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n46: )\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Singleton\n50: \n51: ```go\n52: var (\n53:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n54:     provider      Store\n55: )\n56: \n57: func Storage() Store\n58: func initStore() error\n59: ```\n60: \n61: - `Storage()` calls `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`; on error `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`.\n62: \n63: ### Sandbox document type\n64: \n65: Stored JSON unmarshals to `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo`:\n66: \n67: ```go\n68: type SandboxInfo struct {\n69:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n70:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n71:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n72:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n73:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n74:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n75:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n76:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n77:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n78: }\n79: \n80: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n81:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n82:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n83:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n84: }\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ## Redis implementation (`store_redis.go`)\n88: \n89: ### Struct\n90: \n91: ```go\n92: type redisStore struct {\n93:     cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n94:     sessionPrefix        string\n95:     expiryIndexKey       string\n96:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n97: }\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### Fixed key patterns\n101: \n102: | Field | Value |\n103: |-------|--------|\n104: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` |\n105: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` |\n106: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` |\n107: \n108: ### Connection options (`makeRedisOptions`)\n109: \n110: ```go\n111: return &redisv9.Options{\n112:     Addr:     redisAddr,     // REDIS_ADDR\n113:     Password: redisPassword, // REDIS_PASSWORD\n114: }, nil\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ### Environment variables (Redis)\n118: \n119: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n120: |----------|----------|--------|\n121: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | |\n122: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | Case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"` |\n123: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | Default `redis` |\n124: \n125: ### Operations summary\n126: \n127: | Method | Redis commands |\n128: |--------|----------------|\n129: | `Ping` | `PING` ŌåÆ expect `PONG` |\n130: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `GET session:{id}` |\n131: | `StoreSandbox` | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD session:expiry`, `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n132: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET key value XX` |\n133: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` |\n134: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` then pipeline GETs |\n135: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity ...` then pipeline GETs |\n136: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `GET` (existence), then `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n137: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n138: \n139: - `List*` with `limit <= 0` returns `nil, nil`.\n140: - `sessionKey(id)` ŌåÆ `sessionPrefix + sessionID`.\n141: \n142: ## Valkey implementation (`store_valkey.go`)\n143: \n144: ### Struct\n145: \n146: ```go\n147: type valkeyStore struct {\n148:     cli                  valkey.Client  // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n149:     sessionPrefix        string\n150:     expiryIndexKey       string\n151:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n152: }\n153: ```\n154: \n155: Same string constants as Redis for prefix and ZSET keys.\n156: \n157: ### Connection options (`makeValkeyOptions`)\n158: \n159: ```go\n160: valkeyClientOptions := &valkey.ClientOption{\n161:     InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n162:     Password:    valkeyPassword,\n163: }\n164: ```\n165: \n166: Optional: `DisableCache` from `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, must be true); `ForceSingleClient` from `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, must be true).\n167: \n168: ### Environment variables (Valkey)\n169: \n170: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n171: |----------|----------|--------|\n172: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated list ŌåÆ `InitAddress` |\n173: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n174: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `DisableCache` |\n175: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `ForceSingleClient` |\n176: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | Case-insensitive |\n177: \n178: ### Operations summary\n179: \n180: | Method | Valkey API |\n181: |--------|------------|\n182: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` ŌåÆ string `PONG` |\n183: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` ŌåÆ bytes; `IsValkeyNil` ŌåÆ `ErrNotFound` |\n184: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity |\n185: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET ... XX`; success requires `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n186: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity |\n187: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` |\n188: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same on `last_activity` key |\n189: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key ŌåÆ int64 must be 1; then `Zadd` |\n190: | `Close` | `vs.cli.Close()` then return nil |\n191: \n192: ### ZSET score semantics\n193: \n194: - **Expiry index:** score = `float64(sandboxRedis.ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store.\n195: - **Last activity:** score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`; `float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`.\n196: \n197: ### MGET note (Valkey)\n198: \n199: - `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` builds all `session:{id}` keys and uses single `Mget`; comment states keys should be in same slot (deployment consideration).\n200: \n201: ## Dependencies (store package imports)\n202: \n203: - `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n204: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n205: - `k8s.io/klog/v2` (Valkey options logging)\n206: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n\n(End of file - total 206 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Store ŌĆö Design\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` ŌĆö versions in sandbox-orchestration `design.md`.\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n\n### Store interface (exact signatures)\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-store/design.md","time":{"start":1775852794486,"end":1775852794504}}}}
