{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852841290,"sessionID":"ses_286ed4f0bffefmfnGF4OM7xCV9","part":{"id":"prt_d7913e8f0001tGbn0vH233AsPa","messageID":"msg_d791332b6001pmTky27Bv8STnk","sessionID":"ses_286ed4f0bffefmfnGF4OM7xCV9","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-cdf0d200c9aa43cea8fda5d2a067e4b0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-012 Delta-Spec\n\n## Purpose\nDefine the session storage interface for the AgentCube project, providing a unified Store interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers for persisting sandbox metadata, indexing sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection.\n\n## Base Specs\n- deployment/client-go.md: Kubernetes client library for runtime API types (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n- session-store/design.md: Session store design including Store interface, Redis/Valkey implementations, and key patterns\n- session-store/spec.md: Session store specification with detailed requirements and scenarios\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Store interface contract\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n\n#### Scenario: GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves session data\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:abc` exists with sandbox JSON data\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` is called\n- **THEN** it returns `*types.SandboxInfo` unmarshaled from the stored JSON\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox persists new session\n- **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with non-zero `ExpiresAt`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** it executes SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSandbox modifies existing session\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:abc` exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** it updates only the session JSON value using SET with XX flag\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes session\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:abc` exists\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` is called\n- **THEN** it deletes session key and removes session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline\n\n#### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired sessions\n- **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n- **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n- **THEN** it selects members with scores from negative infinity through `before.Unix()`, limited to `limit` entries\n\n#### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes returns inactive sessions\n- **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n- **WHEN** executed\n- **THEN** members with last-activity score Ōēż `before.Unix()` are returned up to `limit`\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity updates activity timestamp\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:abc` exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** it ZADDs the session id with score `at.Unix()` to the last_activity ZSET\n\n#### Scenario: Close closes connection\n- **GIVEN** an open store connection\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** the underlying client connection is closed\n\n### Requirement: Not found semantics\nThe system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n\n#### Scenario: Get missing session\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs\n- **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n\n#### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n- **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n- **THEN** return `ErrNotFound`\n\n### Requirement: Session key naming\nThe system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n\n#### Scenario: Key construction\n- **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n- **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n- **THEN** the string key is `session:abc`\n\n### Requirement: Expiry index\nThe system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL add the member with the sandbox expiry score. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL remove the member.\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to expiry index\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** ZADD adds session id with score `1234567890.0` to `session:expiry`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete removes from expiry index\n- **GIVEN** a session id in `session:expiry` ZSET\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` succeeds\n- **THEN** ZREM removes the session id from `session:expiry`\n\n### Requirement: Last-activity index\nThe system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD with score `time.Now().Unix()` on initial store. `UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD with the provided timestamp (or now if zero). `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM the member.\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to last-activity index\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox is being stored\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** ZADD adds session id with score `time.Now().Unix()` to `session:last_activity`\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity with explicit timestamp\n- **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Unix(1234567890, 0))` is called\n- **WHEN** the ZADD executes\n- **THEN** the score is set to `1234567890.0`\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity with zero time\n- **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Time{})` is called\n- **WHEN** the ZADD executes\n- **THEN** the score is set to `time.Now().Unix()`\n\n### Requirement: StoreSandbox atomicity and validation\nThe system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch errors.\n\n#### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n- **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n\n#### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** error indicates expiry time is required\n\n#### Scenario: Atomic pipeline execution\n- **GIVEN** all parameters are valid\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` executes\n- **THEN** SETNX, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity execute atomically; failure of any command fails the entire operation\n\n### Requirement: UpdateSandbox semantics\nThe system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries in this operation.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing key on update\n- **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs\n- **THEN** Redis: SETXX returns false ŌåÆ error `key not exists`; Valkey: response not OK ŌåÆ same error class\n\n#### Scenario: Update succeeds for existing key\n- **GIVEN** session key `session:abc` exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` updates the sandbox\n- **THEN** the JSON value is updated and expiry/last-activity indices are unchanged\n\n### Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID cleanup\nThe system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n\n#### Scenario: Full removal\n- **GIVEN** an existing session\n- **WHEN** delete succeeds\n- **THEN** GET session key returns not found and ZSETs no longer contain the member\n\n### Requirement: List loaders tolerate missing keys\nWhen listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing (Redis pipeline GET nil, Valkey MGET empty string) without failing the whole batch.\n\n#### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member\n- **GIVEN** a session id in ZSET without a hash/string value\n- **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\n- **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice\n\n#### Scenario: List with zero limit\n- **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)`\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** it returns `nil, nil`\n\n### Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity preconditions\nThe system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n\n#### Scenario: Empty session id rejected\n- **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at)` is called\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** error indicates session id cannot be empty\n\n#### Scenario: Session existence verification\n- **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n- **THEN** it verifies existence via GET/Exists before ZADD and returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\nThe system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n\n#### Scenario: Default redis\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n- **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit redis provider\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=redis`\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n- **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit valkey provider\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n- **THEN** Valkey implementation is constructed\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid provider type\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=invalid`\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error indicating invalid store type\n\n#### Scenario: Case-insensitive provider type\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=REDIS` or `STORE_TYPE=Valkey`\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n- **THEN** provider is selected correctly (case-insensitive)\n\n### Requirement: Redis environment and password policy\nThe system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n\n#### Scenario: Password required by default\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set and `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n- **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n\n#### Scenario: Password optional when flag set\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n- **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization succeeds with empty password\n\n#### Scenario: Missing REDIS_ADDR fails\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is not set\n- **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error indicating REDIS_ADDR is required\n\n### Requirement: Valkey environment and options\nThe system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses split for `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n\n#### Scenario: Comma-separated addresses parsed\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=host1:6379,host2:6379,host3:6379`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `InitAddress` is `[]string{\"host1:6379\", \"host2:6379\", \"host3:6379\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Optional client flags\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` and `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `DisableCache` is true and `ForceSingleClient` is true on `ClientOption`\n\n#### Scenario: Password optional when flag set\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` set, `VALKEY_PASSWORD` empty, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n- **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization succeeds with empty password\n\n### Requirement: Singleton access\nThe system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n\n#### Scenario: Single initialization\n- **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()`\n- **WHEN** they run concurrently\n- **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n\n#### Scenario: Fatal error on init failure\n- **GIVEN** initialization fails (e.g., connection refused)\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n- **THEN** klog.Fatalf is called and the application exits\n\n### Requirement: SandboxInfo type\nThe system SHALL use `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo` as the document type for stored JSON.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxInfo fields persisted\n- **GIVEN** a `SandboxInfo` with `SandboxID=\"sb123\"`, `SessionID=\"abc\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** JSON is stored with fields `{\"sandboxId\":\"sb123\",\"sessionId\":\"abc\",\"expiresAt\":1234567890,...}`\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxInfo unmarshaled correctly\n- **GIVEN** stored JSON `{\"sandboxId\":\"sb123\",\"sessionId\":\"abc\",\"expiresAt\":1234567890,...}`\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` is called\n- **THEN** returns `*SandboxInfo` with fields correctly unmarshaled\n\n### Requirement: Store error definition\nThe system SHALL define package-level error `ErrNotFound` with message `store: not found`.\n\n#### Scenario: ErrNotFound is exported\n- **GIVEN** the store package is imported\n- **WHEN** caller compares error\n- **THEN** they can use `errors.Is(err, store.ErrNotFound)` to check for not found errors\n\n### Requirement: Provider type constants\nThe system SHALL define constants `redisStoreType` and `valkeyStoreType` for provider type comparison.\n\n#### Scenario: Constants are defined\n- **GIVEN** the store package is imported\n- **WHEN** code checks provider type\n- **THEN** constants `redisStoreType = \"redis\"` and `valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"` are available","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775852841277,"end":1775852841287}}}}
